/a><br><a href=\"../time/index.htm\">Time</a><br><a href=\"../ring/index.htm\">Tolkien</a><br><a href=\"../ufo/index.htm\">UFOs</a><br><a href=\"../utopia/index.htm\">Utopia</a><br><a href=\"../wmn/index.htm\">Women</a><br><a href=\"../woe/index.htm\">Wisdom of the East</a><br><a href=\"../zor/index.htm\">Zoroastrianism</a><br></span> </td> <td valign=\"top\" width=\"470\"> <table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" valign=\"top\"><tbody><tr><td> <span class=\"ista-content\"> <center> <a href=\"../index.htm\">Sacred-texts home</a> <br><a href=\"../neu/index.htm\">Legends &amp; Sagas</a> <a href=\"../pag/index.htm\">Paganism</a> <a href=\"../egy/index.htm\">Egypt</a> <a href=\"../ane/index.htm\">Ancient Near East</a><br><a href=\"../cdshop/index.htm\">Buy CD-ROM</a> <a href=\"../books/cla.htm\">Buy Books: Classics</a> </center> <hr><center> <table width=\"100\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"50%\"> <img src=\"img/sounion0.jpg\" alt=\"Temple of Posiedon at Sounioun, (c) J.B. Hare 2002\" height=\"256\"></td> <td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"50%\"> <span class=\"splashtitle\">The Classics</span> </td> </tr></tbody></table></center> <hr><center> <a href=\"#greek\">Greek Texts</a> <a href=\"#roman\">Roman Texts</a><br> <a href=\"#general\">General Books</a><br><a href=\"#aboutphotos\">About the Photos...</a> </center> <hr><p>This section contains texts from ancient Greece and Rome, primarily about Classical Pagan beliefs. However, any text which has survived from this period of antiquity is, by definition, a classic. Many of these texts were only saved from the flames of the dark ages in locations remote from Rome and Athens, such as the legendary city of Timbuktu in central Africa, Irish monastaries, and by Islamic scholars in centers of learning as Baghdad. </p> <hr><a name=\"greek\"><h2 align=\"CENTER\">Greek</h2></a> <p> HOMER<br><a href=\"homer/index.htm\">Works of Homer</a>:<br><a href=\"#\" onclick=\"window.open('../cdshop/index.htm